[{"body": "PT RMK Investama increased its stake in PT RMK Energy TBK to 45.71% by acquiring 900 million shares, becoming the controlling shareholder, while PT MNC Asia Holding TBK also boosted its ownership in PT RMK Energy TBK to 9.68%. Meanwhile, several other investors and companies made notable share purchases and reductions, including PT Abadi Kreasi Unggul Nusantara, which released 205.53 million shares of PT Sinergi Inti Andalan Prima TBK, marking the largest share reduction.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "industrials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51017/rmk-investama-acquires-rmk-energy-rmke-shares", "sub_sector": ["multi-sector-holdings", "oil-gas-coal", "telecommunication"], "tags": ["Mergers & Acquisitions", "Executive Changes", "Market Trends", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["RMKE.JK", "BHIT.JK", "INET.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-09-27T11:30:08", "title": "PT RMK Investama and other investors make significant share purchases and sales in various Indonesian companies."}, {"body": "PT Pembangunan Perumahan Tbk is on track to complete the Nusantara Capital City Airport project by the end of this year, with 73% of the 3,000m runway construction already finished. The airport, which can currently accommodate three narrow-body aircrafts or one narrow-body plane and three helicopters, is projected to house seven narrow-body aircrafts and three wide-body planes in the future.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "infrastructures", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51016/ptpp-speeds-ikn-airport-completion", "sub_sector": ["transportation-infrastructure"], "tags": ["IDX", "Market Trends", "Energy Commodities", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-09-27T11:19:18", "title": "PT PP Targets Completion of Nusantara Capital City Airport Project by End of This Year"}, {"body": "PT Esta Indonesia TBK (Nest) has injected IDR 6 billion in additional capital into its subsidiary, PT Tunas Esta Indonesia (TEI), increasing TEI's issued and paid-up capital from IDR 3.5 billion to IDR 9.5 billion. This investment is in line with Nest's IPO proceeds utilization plan, which allocates 18.57% of the funds for capital investment in TEI, a company engaged in swallow farming and wholesale agriculture products.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "consumer-non-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51015/esta-indonesia-grant-subsidiary-extra-capital-idr", "sub_sector": ["food-beverage"], "tags": ["IPO", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["CPRO.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-09-27T11:15:39", "title": "PT Esta Indonesia invests IDR 6 billion in subsidiary PT Tunas Esta Indonesia to boost its capital."}, {"body": "Foreign investors purchased a net 456.94 million shares on Thursday, September 26, with the largest share purchase record held by PT GoTo Gojek Tokopedia Tbk at 816.63 million shares. Meanwhile, foreign investors sold a significant number of shares in companies such as PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia Tbk (-544.21 million shares) and PT Bumi Resources Tbk (-77.58 million shares), among others.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51014/entering-green-zone-foreign-volume-closed-shares", "sub_sector": ["banks", "software-it-services"], "tags": ["Foreign Investor", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["GOTO.JK", "BBRI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-09-27T10:52:41", "title": "Foreigners Buy 456.94 Million Shares in Indonesian Market, Led by Goto Gojek Tokopedia and Buana Lintas Lautan"}, {"body": "The Jakarta Composite Stock Price Index (JCI) slipped to 7,662.60 at 9:05 am WIB, down from its opening position of 7,721.55, with other indices such as LQ45, IDX30, IDX80, and IDXESG also experiencing declines. Several blue-chip stocks, including PT Chandra Asri Pacific TBK and PT Bank Mandiri TBK, fell, while others like PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia TBK and PT Aneka Tambang TBK remained in the green zone.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51013/jci-plummeted-morning-session", "sub_sector": ["banks", "basic-materials"], "tags": ["IDX Composite", "LQ45", "IDX30", "Market Trends", "IDX", "Bearish"], "tickers": ["TPIA.JK", "BMRI.JK", "BBRI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-09-27T10:19:23", "title": "Jakarta Composite Stock Price Index Slips Following Opening Bell, Dragged Down by Decline in Blue-Chip Stocks"}, {"body": "PT Buyung Poetra Sembada Tbk's Dailymeal products saw a 145% year-on-year sales increase in the first half of 2024, surpassing its 10% sales target. The company aims to capitalize on the growing demand for healthy food products, with its Dailymeal range, which includes maize-based rice, cassava rice, and brown rice, distributed through its subsidiary, PT Hoki Distribusi Niaga.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "consumer-non-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51007/hoki-eyes-healthy-rice-market-dailymeal-products", "sub_sector": ["food-beverage"], "tags": ["Earnings Report", "Market Trends", "IDX", "Grains", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["HOKI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-09-26T13:11:54", "title": "PT Buyung Poetra Sembada Tbk eyes healthy food market with its Dailymeal products."}, {"body": "PT Info Media Digital, a subsidiary of PT Tempo Inti Media Tbk, has secured IDR 21.18 billion in investment financing from the Media Development Investment Fund through a convertible performance debenture with a maturity date of December 31, 2028. The funding is expected to strengthen PT Info Media Digital's operational capacity, complete ongoing projects, and support business expansion into more strategic segments, while also reinforcing its capital structure.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51001/tempo-inti-media-subsidiary-receives-idr-financing-mdif", "sub_sector": ["financing-service"], "tags": ["Fintech", "Debt", "Bonds", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-09-25T18:52:08", "title": "PT Info Media Digital secures IDR 21.18 billion investment financing facility from Media Development Investment Fund."}, {"body": "Foreign investors purchased a net 622.56 million shares on Tuesday, September 24, with digital company PT GoTo Gojek Tokopedia Tbk being the most acquired with 382.23 million shares, followed by PT Buana Lintas Lautan Tbk and PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia Tbk. On the other hand, shares of PT Bumi Resources Tbk and PT Barito Renewables Energy Tbk were sold, resulting in net volumes of -124.53 million shares and -134.93 million shares, respectively.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51000/foreign-buying-volume-surges-foreign-volume-surplus-shares", "sub_sector": ["banks", "oil-gas-coal", "software-it-services"], "tags": ["Foreign Investor", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["GOTO.JK", "BULL.JK", "BBRI.JK", "BREN.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-09-25T18:13:31", "title": "Foreign investors net buy 622.56 million shares in Indonesian market, led by digital company PT GoTo Gojek Tokopedia Tbk."}, {"body": "PT MNC Digital Entertainment acquired a 9.09% stake in PT Tripar Multivision Plus through a private placement of 619.42 million shares, while controller Raam Punjabi's shareholding decreased from 77.33% to 70.3%. Meanwhile, other notable transactions included PT Asuransi Jiwa IFG acquiring 537.02 million shares of PT PP Properti, and PT Sinar Mas Cakrawala buying 5.46 million shares of PT Sinar Mas Multiartha.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/50999/mnc-digital-claims-multivision-raam-shares", "sub_sector": ["holding-investment-companies", "media-entertainment", "properties-real-estate"], "tags": ["Mergers & Acquisitions", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["MSIN.JK", "RAAM.JK", "PPRO.JK", "SMMA.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-09-25T18:10:55", "title": "PT Tripar Multivision Plus TBK Welcomes New Investor MNC Digital Entertainment with 9.09% Stake Acquisition"}, {"body": "PT Bank UOB Indonesia aims to achieve a 20% year-on-year credit growth rate by the end of 2024, exceeding the industry's projected growth rate of 10-12%. The bank also targets another 20% credit growth in 2025, driven by its focus on facilitating international transactions and attracting foreign investment, with the industry expected to close in on 15% credit growth.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/50998/uob-confident-credit-growth-projection", "sub_sector": ["alternative-energy", "apparel-luxury-goods", "automobiles-components"], "tags": ["Interest Rates", "IDX", "Financial Ratios", "Market Trends", "Foreign Investor", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["AALI.JK", "ABMM.JK", "ACES.JK", "ACST.JK", "